summary:
I am a 27 year old buyer coordinator at C.I.V. Superunie. In this position I make sure that the process of buying runs smoothly and I support wherever possible. 

I graduated from the Master Development and Rural Innovation at Wageningen University. This master gave me a good insight in the agricultural development sector and allowed me to do a MSc thesis in the ICT4BXW project in Rwanda and a minor thesis research with the Maziwa Zaidi project in Tanzania.

Before Wageningen, I studied International Food and Agribusiness at HAS University of Applied sciences. In this bachelor I was able to do and internship at the Embassy of the Netherlands in Kigali, Rwanda. I was working at the agricultural office on investment opportunities for Dutch agribusinesses. My graduation project was for Agribusiness Development Centre in Uganda focussed on digital innovations for smallholder farmers and farmer based organisations.

I am open-minded, curious and always willing to learn more. I am an motivated, flexible and straightforward person who is willing to work hard for results.
